# REQ-01 golden dry-run sequence — the receipt every factory action must leave.
#
# One line = one flow command's emission, in session order:
#   kickoff → phase-done → review → qa → commit → ship
#
# A "step" is one command's own emissions: order-insensitive WITHIN a command, strict
# ACROSS commands (PLAN REQ-01). kickoff and phase-done each emit TWO kinds — their core
# receipt plus an approval.requested sign-off gate (REQ-06) — in an order the command markdown
# pins, so this stays a deterministic flat ordered list and exact-match holds. If a command's
# intra-command order ever became non-deterministic, this file would split into per-command
# blocks and the test's comparison would relax ordering inside them.
#
# Lifecycle events from the SessionStart/End/PostToolUse hook fragments are NOT here — this
# golden is the command-level flow chain only (assumptions-ledger row 1: the whole point is
# that hook fragments alone do NOT produce these kinds).
kickoff.done
approval.requested
phase.closed
approval.requested
review.completed
qa.completed
commit.done
ship.done
